GenAI Specialist - Technical Assignment
Appendix I - Requirement for identification documentation

Denmark:

For Danish citizens, 1) a copy of the photo ID (e.g. personal information page of the passport) 
and 2) a copy of the front side of the health insurance card (sundhedskort).
For non Danish citizens, 1) a copy of the photo ID (e.g. personal information page of the 
passport), 2) a copy of the front side of the health insurance card (sundhedskort) and 3) a 
copy of the residence permit card (both sides).

Sweden:

For Swedish citizens, 1) a copy of the photo ID (e.g., driving license, national ID card issued by 
Swedish Police, or ID card issued by Swedish Skatteverket).
For EU/EEA citizens, 1) a copy of the photo ID (e.g. personal information page of the 
passport), and 2a) proof of residence address document or 2b) copy of ID card, issued by the 
Skatteverket.
For non-EU citizens, a copy of the photo ID (e.g. personal information page of the passport), 
2a) proof of residence address document or 2b) copy of ID card, issued by the Skatteverket, 
and 3) copy of residence permit or visa.

Norway

For Norwegian citizens, 1) a copy of the photo ID (e.g., driving license, national ID card).
For EU/EEA citizens, 1) a copy of the photo ID (e.g. personal information page of the passport) 
and 2a) copy of the national ID card or 2b) proof of issued D-number.
For non-EU citizens, a copy of the photo ID (e.g. personal information page of the passport), 
2b) proof of issued D-number, and 3) copy of residence permit or visa.

Finland

For Finnish citizens, 1) a copy of the photo ID (e.g., national ID card).
For EU/EEA citizens, 1) a copy of the photo ID (e.g. personal information page of the passport) 
and 2) proof of issued personal identity code.
For non-EU citizens, 1) a copy of the photo ID (e.g. personal information page of the passport) 
and 2) proof of issued personal identity code, and 3) copy of residence permit or visa.
